text: is the name of a Japanese artificial satellite which was put into orbit. The launch was a project of the Institute of Space and Astronautical Science of the University of Tokyo. The satellite was sent into orbit on February 24, 1975.JAXA, "Catalogue of ISAS Missions" ; retrieved 2012-4-2. It entered the atmosphere and burned up on 29 June 1980. == References == == Other websites == * Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA), Taiyo (SPRATS) mission profile Category:Japanese satellites Category:Spacecraft launched in the 1970s
